      <div class="block__section">
        <h2 class="h2">Why should I donate to the Big Change Fund?</h2>
        <p>Giving money to people begging on the street doesn’t help individuals move away from sleeping rough, or address the complicated range of reasons which made them homeless.</p>
        <p>Choosing to support the Big Change Fund is the most effective way to make sure your money is used in a way which directly helps people who are homeless change their lives.</p>
        <p class="text-center">
          <a href="http://campaign.justgiving.com/charity/forevermanchester/bigchangemcr" class="btn btn--brand-e btn--full">
            <span class="btn__text">Donate to Big Change</span>
          </a>
        </p>
      </div>

      {{>divider class="is-hidden--smallscreen"}}

      <div class="block__section">
        <h2 class="h2">What happens to my donation?</h2>
        <p>Your donation joins the central Big Change funding pot which includes donations made by other kind hearted folk and organisations.</p>
        <p>We have a list of charities and organisations who have agreed to be Big Change partners and because these agencies work directly with people who are homeless, they make sure your donation gives maximum benefit.</p>
        <p>Individuals who are homeless can access the fund through these charities and organisations, and after working together to identify what items are needed to help build a new life, they send us an application form. Depending on the amount needed, there are two levels of fund requests to help an individual move away from sleeping rough.</p>
      </div>

